  notes:
    - "This spec covers: threading.Barrier.__name__ 'Barrier'; threading.Barrier.__module__ 'threading'; threading.Barrier.__bases__[0].__name__ 'object'; threading.Barrier.__bases__.__len__() 1; threading.Barrier.wait.__qualname__ 'Barrier.wait'; threading.Barrier.reset.__qualname__ 'Barrier.reset'; threading.Barrier.abort.__qualname__ 'Barrier.abort'; threading.Barrier.__init__.__qualname__ 'Barrier.__init__' (Wave 289)."
    - "threading.Barrier.__name__ == 'Barrier' — Barrier is a Python class defined in Lib/threading.py; its simple class name is 'Barrier'. Verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "threading.Barrier.__module__ == 'threading' — Barrier is defined in Lib/threading.py; its __module__ attribute is 'threading'. Verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "threading.Barrier.__bases__[0].__name__ == 'object' — Barrier inherits directly from object (not from any other threading class); __bases__[0].__name__ is 'object'. Verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "threading.Barrier.__bases__.__len__() == 1 — Barrier has exactly one base class (object); __bases__ is a one-element tuple. Verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "threading.Barrier.wait.__qualname__ == 'Barrier.wait' — Barrier.wait blocks until the barrier is full or a timeout expires; __qualname__ is 'Barrier.wait'. Verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "threading.Barrier.reset.__qualname__ == 'Barrier.reset' — Barrier.reset resets the barrier to its initial empty state; __qualname__ is 'Barrier.reset'. Verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "threading.Barrier.abort.__qualname__ == 'Barrier.abort' — Barrier.abort puts the barrier into a broken state; __qualname__ is 'Barrier.abort'. Verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "threading.Barrier.__init__.__qualname__ == 'Barrier.__init__' — Barrier.__init__ initialises the barrier for the given number of parties; __qualname__ is 'Barrier.__init__'. Verified with Python 3.14.3."
